cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.SD, cs.AI, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a modification to the standard RNN architecture, which is a type of neural network. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper deals with sequence prediction and classification, which are common problems in machine learning. 
- cs.SD (Sound) is a possible category as one of the tasks tested in the paper is audio signal generation. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper deals with improving the performance of RNNs, which are commonly used in AI applications. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category as the paper deals with a modification to the RNN architecture that partitions the hidden layer into separate modules, which can be seen as a control system.
